rComments: Amazing Professor! The concepts that he teaches in BIO361 are incredibly hard, but he does an excellent job at explaining them. He is very accessible for help or questions and does an amazing job in lecture!
I think he's a tough cookie, but he's a good professor.  He's very clear.  And he pushes his students to to more and be better.
He is a horrible prof. The class average is usually a reflection of how good a prof is, well over half the class failed!! Take a easier stats course...stats220!!

He didn't give part marks in BIO360 which made people hate him. He is clear in describing content, but the subject matter is difficult to grasp.  You have to put a lot of effort in understanding the concepts. He is not as bad a guy as he came off in bio360.

I totaly disagree with the last person. He is not a good professor at all. I got a decent mark in his class and I still think he is an unfair professor. He does not know how to explain concepts clearly. The textbook is a better teacher than him!!

I think other people who are commenting did not do well in his course. I disagree. Statistics are confusing and difficult to explain, but I have never met anyone better at explaining them. Be prepared to work (it's University people) but you will absolutly understand stats if you do. I went on to do research with him after the course.  Awsome prof.
The worst prof at UTM. He is not fair in his marking and doesn't do anything when half the class fails. The worst learning experience at UTM.
This prof does not know how to teach and he is very unfair! Goodluck to people wanting to take his class!
